included.description:
I was hired on a six-month internship with Pearson Education.
- Assisted a senior UX researcher in a 5-month instructor diary study. I gave suggestions on what UX metrics to use (e.g., using NPS score in the survey, doing a sentiment analysis, etc.) to efficiently analyze the data by using both quantitative and qualitative analysis. I presented data precisely and concisely in the final report (e.g., demographic charts, instructor portfolio and edited video clips).

- Decided after consulting with senior UX designers to design and conduct an unmoderated first-click study to evaluate a new IA design. I gave suggested design improvements on the next iteration of the product design process and came up with useful questions for focus group interviews.

- Assisted UX researchers and designers in an observation study at Harvard University by taking a 2-week course with the undergrads. This study helped inform an online version of the course. We also interviewed the professors, ultimately providing meaningful feedback on the course and suggested improvements for the future. For instance, we noted difficulties that non-native English speaking students may have during class, that the professor had not thought of yet. 

- Explored semi-structured interviews to understand reading and study behavior on college-level students. Synthesized the interview scripts based on Pearson UX Persona characteristics and summarized overall pain points. Collaborated with a UX Researcher on the final report. 

- Designed surveys in SurveyMonkey after deciding research goals with senior UX researchers. Presented survey results in charts and graphs along with synthesized the open-ended responses to the stakeholders and design teams.

included.summary:
Welcome to visit my portfolio site: www.mengdizux.com.

I have been passionate about research since I was 14 years old when I independently created and executed a social research project. I explored the living conditions and psychological impacts on senior citizens in the city of Wuhan whose adult children needed to work in different cities. I went to different public parks in the city and talked to them individually or in small groups. I found it was difficult for many of them to live in loneliness, and they would spend a lot of time with other seniors at the parks to get through the daytime. I decided to write down what I saw and what they told me in a report and mailed it to the city government, hoping to raise their awareness on these senior citizens. 

10 years later, I completed a Master of Science in Human Factors in Information Design (MSHFID) degree at Bentley University (Feb. 23rd, 2018). Through my graduate program and during my five month UX Research experience with Pearson Education, I have had the opportunity to conduct moderated and unmoderated studies covering a variety of qualitative and quantitative research methods. Now, I am looking for my next professional challenge and opportunity to contribute what I know while also continuing to learn from those around me.
included.headline: User Experience Researcher & Designer
